HEADWORD: Peplus
<hw>Pep"lus</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧p"l⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <grk>pe`plos</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An upper garment
worn by Grecian and Roman women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of kerchief formerly worn by
Englishwomen.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

